<br>
Ghouls are not herd.  Ghouls have to be fed vitae to be maintained.  At least one trait per month per ghoul.  This does not account for any traits that must be used to heal them, etc.  If you want your npc ghouls to learn new abilities and disciplines or develope new resources and backgrounds, these things can be bought with *your* eeps.<br>
<br>
Have some idea of the concept of the World of Darkness, if you want to play this game.  There are abundant resources for the White Wolf game system online and on paper.  You don't have to memorize the rules, but you should have some idea of the world and the creatures in it, OOG, as a player.<br>
<br>
Play nice.  This doesn't mean everyone's characters should be Lawful Good.  This means realize that some things are IC and IG and some are out.  Realize that while we all invest time and energy into this game and our characters, that it is ultimately JUST A GAME.<br>
<br>
While we are giving eeps for Literary posts, there is no direct conversion between how many posts equal how many eeps.  Literary posts are also not a replacement for roleplaying and interacting with the staff and players.<br>
<br>
We will be working on the sub-plots that some players have been running for us.  We have not been able to maintain enough communication about them and some players have been abusing this.  Also various players have come in with plots they have written up and gotten unreasonably upset with us for not allowing them to be run on the fly, regardless of their appropriatness for game.  So from here, basically if we can't run it directly it just isn't going to work.  We thank the players who have been trying to help us with these plots for their time and efforts.<br>
<br>
We have been very generous with the granting of eeps.  We want everyone to be able to develope their characters and have fun.  However, we will be docking points from here on out for abuses of the system and the game staff.<br>
<br>
I think that covers everything, if a bit briskly.<br>
